# File: tests/features/bug-fix-interact-click-css-selector-path-onclick-not-triggered-reliably-vs-uid-click.feature
#
# Generated from: specs/bug-fix-interact-click-css-selector-path-onclick-not-triggered-reliably-vs-uid-click/requirements.md
# Issue: #252
# Type: Defect regression

@regression
Feature: interact click CSS selector path fires onclick handlers
  The `interact click css:<selector>` path previously resolved the element and
  dispatched a mouse event at the button's center but did not trigger the
  element's `onclick` handler, while the UID path and `click-at` at the same
  coordinates did. This was fixed by aligning the CSS-selector resolution
  and dispatch with the UID path.

  # --- Bug Is Fixed ---

  @regression
  Scenario: CSS selector click triggers the onclick-driven DOM mutation
    Given the page "https://the-internet.herokuapp.com/add_remove_elements/" is loaded
    And there are 0 ".added-manually" elements in the DOM
    When I run `agentchrome interact click "css:button[onclick='addElement()']"`
    Then the command exits 0
    And there is 1 ".added-manually" element in the DOM

  # --- Related Behavior Still Works ---

  @regression
  Scenario: UID click still triggers the onclick-driven DOM mutation
    Given the page "https://the-internet.herokuapp.com/add_remove_elements/" is loaded
    And a snapshot has populated the UID map for the "Add Element" button
    And there are 0 ".added-manually" elements in the DOM
    When I run `agentchrome interact click <uid>` for the "Add Element" button
    Then the command exits 0
    And there is 1 ".added-manually" element in the DOM

  @regression
  Scenario: CSS selector click on a navigation link still navigates
    Given a page containing an "<a href>" link resolvable by CSS selector
    When I run `agentchrome interact click "css:<navigation-selector>"`
    Then the command exits 0
    And the response reports "navigated": true
    And the browser URL is the link target
